170
00:17:09,575 --> 00:17:28,527
I myself was, you know, a victim of bias in the healthcare system as a patient and almost died two times during obstetrical issues that I had.

171
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:35,004
And I know for a fact that there was, you know, again, some biases going on.

172
00:17:35,024 --> 00:17:37,765
I was told, oh, you can't be in that much pain, you know.

173
00:17:39,045 --> 00:17:47,887
And when I passed out and came to, the first thing I remember hearing is the nurse telling me there's no way you can be in that much pain, saying, well, I guess you got the attention you wanted, huh?

174
00:17:48,668 --> 00:17:50,688
Like I was attention seeking by passing out.

175
00:17:51,688 --> 00:17:56,650
But I'd lost a liter of blood, so that is why I was unconscious.

176
00:17:59,727 --> 00:18:06,429
It seems like very trivial, but this is the experience of black and brown women, especially in healthcare.

177
00:18:06,609 --> 00:18:11,191
And that hospital, to its credit, has done a lot of work to get better.

178
00:18:11,851 --> 00:18:14,192
